The existing series of lemmas on the continuity of `f : Î± Ã— Î² â†’ Î³` requires Lipschitz continuity in `Î±` and continuity in `Î²`. I add a series of mirror lemmas with the argument positions swapped, i.e. continuity in `Î±` and Lipschitz continuity in `Î²`. This improves usability, for example, in the Picard-LindelÃ¶f theorem, where the time-dependent vector field is typically assumed to be continuous in time (the first component) and Lipschitz continuous in space (the second component).
